description.plain:
Calvin Woods (b. April 3, 1999), professionally known as Calboy, is a rapper from Calumet City, Chicago, Illinois.

Rapping since the 6th grade, he built a hometown fan base with his first mixtape Calboy the Wildboy and breakout, platinum-selling   single “Envy Me” in 2018.

The following year, Calboy signed with RCA Records and released his debut studio album, Wildboy, featuring the hit track “Chariot” with Meek Mill, Young Thug, and Lil Durk. He dropped a follow-up EP, Long Live the Kings, and its deluxe edition in 2020.

description.plain:
Young Thug, Lil Durk & Meek Mill team up to assist CalBoy on “Chariot” a banger produced by the Greek producing twins Nikolas and Alex W. Papamitrou.

The quartet comes with a smooth delivery and deals with topics such as their new money and women, and coming from the corners of high crime neighborhoods to their current luxurious lives.

On August 16, 2019, CalBoy re-released the song as a single, keeping only his verse, the chorus, and Lil Durk’s verse.

songs.title: Adam & Eve

description.plain:
“Adam & Eve” is CalBoy’s love song that is dedicated to his soul mate, who continues to switch on him. CalBoy reflects on her flimsy attitude and the constant change she undergoes.

The biblical story of “Adam and Eve” stems from the Book of Genesis and describes the experiences of the first two people on Earth.
